{"tid":2302079,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"加拿大兩名現任國會議員新民黨Niki Ashtn以及綠黨Paul Manly 首次公開支持釋放孟晚舟","createTime":"2020-11-27T00:29:20.000Z","updateTime":"2020-11-27T02:53:28.000Z","uid":78519,"like":4,"dislike":50,"uniUserReply":27,"replies":[{"pid":"a8814acd7ee65c92bbfb0923548bc6bb9258da92","tid":2302079,"uid":78519,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:29:20.000Z","msg":"香港商報<br />\n<br />\n據南華早報報導，加拿大聯邦國會的兩位眾議員，來自新民黨的尼基&middot;阿什頓(Niki Ashton)、來自綠黨的保羅&middot;曼利(Paul Manly)宣佈，他們公開支持要求釋放孟晚舟的主張，以防止「與中國關係破裂」。<br />\n<img src=\"https://www.citynews1130.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/sites/9/2020/11/23/Meng-Zoom-Manly-1.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citynews1130.com%2Fwp-content%2Fblogs.dir%2Fsites%2F9%2F2020%2F11%2F23%2FMeng-Zoom-Manly-1.jpg&h=dad74fb1&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<img src=\"https://hkcd.com/userfiles/1606178616.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhkcd.com%2Fuserfiles%2F1606178616.jpg&h=ad49967c&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n上週，新民黨與反對派保守黨發起是否禁止中國科技巨頭華為建設加拿大5G互聯網的投票。阿什頓是三位棄權的新民黨議員之一。<br />\n隨後，溫哥華市議員安妮&middot;羅伯茨(Anne Roberts)也宣佈，支持釋放孟晚舟。這是加拿大現任國會議員首次公開表示支持釋放孟晚舟。<br />\n<br />\n 而此前幾天，加拿大總理杜魯多表示，他絕不後悔逮捕孟晚舟。<br />\n<br />\n 20日，外交部發言人趙立堅回應杜魯多言論，表示加拿大領導人不願以本國人民利益為代價去滿足美國的一己私利。<br />\n<br />\n 中方在孟晚舟事件上的立場是明確的、堅定的。必須強調，在已經披露的事實和眾多疑點前，無論加政府如何掩蓋真相、誤導公眾，都絕不會改變孟晚舟事件的政治性質，也絕不會改變加政府在這一事件中扮演美方幫凶和馬前卒的不光彩角色。<br />\n<br />\n 趙立堅表示，越來越多加拿大國內有識之士公開要求加政府獨立自主作出釋放孟晚舟的決定，這其中有政要、律師、法官和前外交官等。中方奉勸加領導人多聽聽他們的正義和理智的呼聲。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3111078/canadian-mps-join-campaign-release-meng-wanzhou-citing\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fdiplomacy%2Farticle%2F3111078%2Fcanadian-mps-join-campaign-release-meng-wanzhou-citing&d=jO1S1Ej7eDj8oQYGBWUFpM5qU0izJB5q5dcgVJazxes%3D&h=f05b1fc7\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3111078/canadian-mps-join-campaign-release-meng-wanzhou-citing</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.citynews1130.com/2020/11/23/paul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citynews1130.com%2F2020%2F11%2F23%2Fpaul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom%2F&d=jO1S1Ej7eDj8oQYGBWUFpM5qU0izJB5q5dcgVJazxes%3D&h=8a4dee8e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.citynews1130.com/2020/11/23/paul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom/</a>"},{"pid":"d215d9fbfab4726c7323083b44ed39b8b4f05f16","tid":2302079,"uid":79117,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:30:28.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"0a97c65046b64ae46a485f662465f8a661d055a7","tid":2302079,"uid":248540,"like":6,"dislike":3,"score":3,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:30:35.000Z","msg":"拜登一上 聯盟就散<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5af1fe22cab8e0ca1399d1f6e71a02c2a5c21f73","tid":2302079,"uid":78519,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:31:02.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.citynews1130.com/2020/11/23/paul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citynews1130.com%2F2020%2F11%2F23%2Fpaul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom%2F&d=jO1S1Ej7eDj8oQYGBWUFpM5qU0izJB5q5dcgVJazxes%3D&h=8a4dee8e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.citynews1130.com/2020/11/23/paul-manly-free-meng-wanzhou-zoom/</a><br />\n<blockquote>SUMMARY<br />\nMP Paul Manly will be participating in the forum along with MP Niki Ashton, lawyer John Philpot<br />\nManly says Meng's arrest in December of 2018 was an act of 'hostage diplomacy' by Donald Trump</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nVANCOUVER (NEWS 1130) &mdash; A B.C. Member of Parliament set to take part in an online forum  &ldquo;Zoom to free Meng Wanzhou&rdquo; says the event isn&rsquo;t a rally for her release but rather a forum to discuss how the Trump administration put Canada in &ldquo;a terrible position.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nGreen MP Paul Manly, who represents Namaimo-Ladysmith will be participating in Tuesday&rsquo;s forum along with MP Niki Ashton, and John Philpot, lawyer and expert in international criminal law.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t consider this a rally to free Meng Wanzhou, I consider this a debate about how we get ourselves out of that situation, and that lies squarely with the Trump administration,&rdquo; he says.<br />\n<br />\nManly says Meng&rsquo;s arrest in December of 2018 was an act of &ldquo;hostage diplomacy&rdquo; by the U.S. and that China retaliated by arresting Michael Kovrig and Michael Spavor soon after.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The Trump administration abused the trust of Canadian authorities and abused international diplomatic norms. The timing of Meng&rsquo;s arrest in Vancouver was a cynical manipulation of the Trump administration,&rdquo; Manly says.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;This whole situation can be laid at the feet of Donald Trump. He is key to everything that happened with Meng Wanzhou and how Michael Spavor and Michael Kovrig ended up in Chinese jail with no light at the end of the tunnel.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<blockquote>Green Party MP @paulmanly confirms he will participate in &quot;Zoom to Free Meng Wanzhou&quot; on Tuesday. Says its a forum to discuss the fate of the &quot;Two Michaels&quot; and how the Trump administration has put Canada in a difficult position. @NEWS1130 <a href=\"http://pic.twitter.com/BJ6KwPLvI4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fpic.twitter.com%2FBJ6KwPLvI4&d=jO1S1Ej7eDj8oQYGBWUFpM5qU0izJB5q5dcgVJazxes%3D&h=49fd3a24\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/BJ6KwPLvI4</a><br />\n<br />\n&mdash; Paul James (@pjimmyradio) November 23, 2020</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nNevertheless, Manly says the position of the federal Green Party caucus is that the U.S. should withdraw its extradition request, and he is hopeful the incoming Biden administration will do so.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We put out a statement in July calling on the federal government to demand that the United States drop criminal charges against Meng Wanzhou and withdraw its extradition requests so that Canada can release her, and that remains my position,&rdquo; he says.<br />\n<br />\nBut Manly says the event should not be understood as an attempt to interfere with or influence extradition proceedings. <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I am putting forward a nuanced position that we&rsquo;re calling on the U.S. government to drop the extradition process. And that&rsquo;s what I&rsquo;m stepping into this event to do, just to talk about the position that we&rsquo;ve put forward. And that is that we need to ask that the U.S. government drop these charges against Meng Wanzhou,&rdquo; he says.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We need to get back to multilateralism, diplomacy, and working together across the international community for peace, good governance, social justice.&rdquo;"},{"pid":"42548b8f04a18c15d31b0ae22f268abeac840563","tid":2302079,"uid":51271,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:32:16.000Z","msg":"商報，即係支那比錢"},{"pid":"543b7fce52deab083254a3081f3e51689304e198","tid":2302079,"uid":196924,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:32:20.000Z","msg":"吓但係而家慢慢走本人同支共都好似唔係太想慢慢走返支國...?"},{"pid":"cfb9ea411ed82e5c27818838165e566a17c59937","tid":2302079,"uid":78519,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"42548b8f04a18c15d31b0ae22f268abeac840563","tid":2302079,"uid":51271,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:32:16.000Z","msg":"商報，即係支那比錢"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-27T00:33:22.000Z","msg":"中文來源係香港商報<br />\n<a href=\"https://hkcd.com/content/2020-11/24/content_1231014.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhkcd.com%2Fcontent%2F2020-11%2F24%2Fcontent_1231014.html&d=jO1S1Ej7eDj8oQYGBWUFpM5qU0i